properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 16 at 3:42AM CST until January 18 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS COLD TONIGHT...
...HEAVY SNOW EXPECTED FRIDAY THROUGH SATURDAY...

.Wind chill values of 20 below to near 40 below zero are
expected this morning.

Snow returns to the forecast for Friday through Saturday, with
widespread accumulating snow, with snowfall amounts of 5 to 10
inches possible. In addition to the snow, gusty southerly winds
will occur Friday into Friday evening and strong northwest winds
will occur Saturday. The wind will cause blowing and drifting
snow.

* WHAT...Heavy snow possible with snow accumulations of 5 to 9
inches possible. Winds could gust as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Iron and Ashland Counties. This includes the Tribal
Lands of the Bad River Reservation.

* WHEN...From Friday afternoon through Saturday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH NOW IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SATURDAY AFTERNOON
